  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC (START): Multisectoral response to the conflict victims in Rwampara health zone,Irumu Territory in Ituri Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By 2 May 2020, an estimated 9000 Internal Displaced People (IDPs) had reached Walu localities in Rwampara health zone, Irumu territory in Ituri province, as a result of civil conflict. Through our international implementing partner HelpAge, Age International supported the 5,000 of the most vulnerable people who had largely settled in unsheltered in public places, with cash assistance.</narrative>
  </description>
